  "description": "Torsten Emil Ekman was a Swedish civil engineer born on September 8th, 1887 in Stockholm. He was married to Emy Sofia Carlquist for 17 years and had two children, Nils and Ulla. He graduated from Chalmers University of Technology in 1909 and worked as an assistant engineer in state agriculture from 1909. He was employed by Gothenburg Port Authority and Street Administration from 1910 to 1913, Stockholm Port Authority from 1913 to 1917, State Waterfall Road from 1917 to 1922, and served as the head engineer for the Road and Highway Administration in Gothenburg from 1922. He also worked on several power line rebuilding projects and served on the Board of Directors for Chalmers Engineering Society from 1939 to 1944. He was awarded the Royal Order of Vasa in 1945. His hobbies included gardening." 
